      "alignment": "unaligned",
      "biography": {
        "value": "\n                        Legends speak of a peculiar breed of dragon that evolved in the kitchens of ancient, decadent feasts. These condiment drakes developed a unique digestive and respiratory system, allowing them to metabolize and expel various sauces and condiments. They are often found near abandoned pantries, spice markets, or regions known for their culinary traditions, guarding their territory with a flavorful, if dangerous, spray.\n                        <hr>\n                        <p><strong>Behavior:</strong> The condiment drake is an instinct-driven creature that seeks out areas with abundant food sources. It uses its breath weapon to incapacitate prey or deter threats, often coating the area in a sticky, pungent mess.</p>\n                        <p><strong>Appearance:</strong> A medium-sized dragon with scales that shimmer in shades of yellow, red, and green, resembling mustard, ketchup, and relish. Its wings are translucent and somewhat sticky, and its breath often carries a faint, vinegary aroma.</p>\n                        <p><strong>Twist:</strong> Despite its noxious breath, the drake's body is surprisingly clean and emits a faint, pleasant scent of herbs.</p>\n                        <p><strong>Habitat:</strong> Kitchens, pantries, abandoned taverns, and areas with strong culinary traditions.</p>\n                        <p><strong>Treasure:</strong> None</p>\n                    "
      },
